Content:
Part of the problem is, that it&#x27;s highly undesirable having to mark every node as rtl, when it should just be inerited.<p>Eventually (<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/%3Adir" rel="nofollow">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/%3Adir</a>) will be able to write it like this:<p><pre><code>    .some-class {
      &:dir(rtl) { margin-right: 1em; }
      &:dir(ltr) { margin-left: 1em; }
    }
</code></pre>
Right now it&#x27;s probably easiest to load an additional stylesheet when a RTL language is used.
